    <h2><a id="More_on_the_Signer_18"></a>More on the Signer</h2>
    <p>The project is a node.js project that use express as the web framework.</p>
    <ol>
        <li><code>npm start</code> is actually run app.js which initiate application variables and modules and start the server (in www/bin)</li>
        <li>app.js register a router (entry point) for all requests that will be <code>http://&lt;this domain&gt;/rollout</code></li>
        <li>Entry point (in routes/rollout.js)</li>
        <li>Call for signing configuration send to <code>http://&lt;this domain&gt;/rollout/sign</code> with method=<code>POST</code> and body is:</li>
    </ol>
    <pre><code class="language-json">{
      "data": {
       //Data that we like to sign with the private key
      },
      certificateMd5: 'd1ff47188bb9ffedd3572e8d2322bc7e', //md5 value generated from running md5 on the certificate registered on rollout dashboard. Ususally act as a key to the private key in a local map.
      callback: "http://localhost:8090/" //The url which you should send the result too.
    }
</code></pre>
    <ol start="5">
        <li>Signer verify the incoming certificate md5 points to a valid public key (reply with error if not)</li>
        <li>Signer sign the incoming data and send it to the callback given in the request.</li>
    </ol>
